# Performance & Optimization Standards

## Core Web Vitals Targets
- **LCP (Largest Contentful Paint)**: < 2.5s
- **FID (First Input Delay)**: < 100ms
- **CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift)**: < 0.1
- **Overall Lighthouse Score**: 90+

## Next.js Optimization
- Use App Router for optimal performance
- Implement proper loading.tsx and error.tsx files
- Use Next.js Image component for optimized images
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting

## Image Optimization
- Compress images before adding to public/
- Use appropriate image formats (WebP, AVIF)
- Implement lazy loading for below-fold images
- Use responsive images with proper srcset
- Optimize SVG files and inline when possible

## Bundle Optimization
- Minimize bundle size with tree shaking
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Implement proper code splitting strategies
- Monitor bundle analyzer output
- Remove unused dependencies regularly

## Caching & Performance
- Implement proper HTTP caching headers
- Use Next.js built-in optimization features
- Minimize third-party script impact
- Implement service worker if needed
- Use CDN for static assets

## Monitoring & Testing
- Regular Lighthouse audits
- Monitor Core Web Vitals in production
- Test performance on various devices
- Use Next.js Analytics for insights
- Regular performance budget reviews
